article.headline: Wyoming seals win in final minute over San Jose St, 77-74
article.linkText: Wyoming seals win in final minute over San Jose St, 77-74
article.story: LARAMIE, Wyo. -- Josh Adams scored 28 points and added six assists to lead Wyoming to a 77-74 win over San Jose State on Wednesday night. Adams finished just 6 of 16 from the field but hit 15 of 17 free throws. San Jose State led 42-41 at the half and neither team held more than a six-point lead over the final 20 minutes. Adams hit a free throw and Jordan Naughton made a layup for a 75-72 Cowboys lead with 2:03 left. Brandon Clarke answered with a dunk for the Spartans to cut it back to one. But Naughton responded with a dunk of his own to make it 77-74, and Princeton Onwas turned it over on the Spartans final possession to seal the win for Wyoming (14-17, 7-11 Mountain West). Jason McManamen finished with 16 for Wyoming. Frank Rogers led San Jose State (8-21, 3-14) with 15 points.
